   [$ (^Emil.^) $] Company is a very good thing, Madam, but I 
Wonder you do not love it a little more Chosen.
   [$ (^L. Town.^) $] 'Tis good to have an universal taste, we 
Should love Wit, but for Variety, be able to divert 
Our selves with the Extravagancies of those who want it.
   [$ (^Med.^) $] Fools will make you laugh.
   [$ (^Emil.^) $] For once or twice! but the repetition of their
